curam.util.common.plugin
Interface PlugInContainer<T extends PlugInContainer<?>>

Type Parameters:
T - The specific type of this plug-in container used as the type for the parent and child relationships.
All Superinterfaces:
java.io.Serializable
All Known Subinterfaces:
ClientDomain, Domain, Style
public interface PlugInContainer<T extends PlugInContainer<?>>
extends java.io.Serializable

A interface describing immutable classes that can contain plug-ins and that will manage the life cycle of those plug-ins. Containers can optionally contain other containers to form a tree structure. A typical, real-world, container is described by the Domain interface.

getPlugIn

PlugIn getPlugIn(java.lang.String plugInName,
                 curam.util.common.plugin.PlugInTarget target)
                 throws PlugInException
Gets the named plug-in object for the given plug-in target. If the container does not have the plug-in, it will return a plug-in inherited from its parent (if available). An inherited plug-in will also inherit a configuration from its parent (if any).

Parameters:
plugInName - The name of the plug-in.
target - The target container of the requested plug-in. Use SELF to get the plug-in that applies to this container and DESCENDANT to get the plug-in that a child container should inherit. These plug-ins may be different.
Returns:
The plug-in object, may be null.
Throws:
PlugInException - If the plug-in name is null.
